    {"slug":"past-irregular-1","topic":"Past Simple","topicKey":"past","badge":"../assets/badges/a2-past.png","title":"Past Simple — Irregular Verbs (go, have, see)","canDo":"Talk about common past experiences with irregular verbs.","ruleHTML":"<p>Irregular verbs have special past forms: go→<b>went</b>, have→<b>had</b>, see→<b>saw</b>.</p>","examplesHTML":"<ul><li>We <b>went</b> to Paris.</li><li>I <b>had</b> lunch at 1.</li><li>They <b>saw</b> a film.</li></ul>","challengeSeconds":60,"nextSlug":"past-negatives","questions":[{"prompt":"She ___ (go) to the gym yesterday.","options":[{"text":"went","correct":true},{"text":"goed"},{"text":"go"}]},{"prompt":"I ___ (have) a meeting at 9.","options":[{"text":"had","correct":true},{"text":"haved"},{"text":"has"}]},{"prompt":"They ___ (see) the new cafe.","options":[{"text":"saw","correct":true},{"text":"seed"},{"text":"seen"}]}]},

